arts.ttl: No laughing matter as Stevenage are beaten 3-0 at Stockport County
arts.sum: They fell behind when Jayden Fevrier's effort deflected off Charlie Goode and wrong-footed Murphy Cooper in the first half and then Kyle Wootton and Jack Diamond finished the job off in the second period. And as if to prove what could happen when you do that, Stockport managed two shots all half and just one on target, the latter the one from Fevrier that opened the scoring.

arts.ttl: Stockport boost their League One play-off hopes with win over Stevenage
Boss hoping for 'big things quite soon' from Stevenage wonderkid Ryan Doherty
arts.sum: Chairman Phil Wallace also hinted at Doherty's imminent debut at the recent fans' forum while at the same time giving an insight into the view of the academy and its importance. He said: "Before we came bottom of League Two, giving minutes to young boys was really important to me, in terms of the academy.
